8.—(1) The Department may remove from any register kept by them under this Act any premises entered therein—


(a) if the premises have been erroneously or fraudulently entered in the register;

(b) if the premises, owing to a change in the character of the business, or otherwise, have ceased to be capable of registration;

(c) if at any time the conditions of registration applicable to the premises or the machinery or plant therein are not complied with; or

(d) if there is a contravention of any of the regulations of this Act applicable to the business carried on upon the premises.

